doc.previous: In the third quarter of 2009, there were 278,189 delinquent loans, 80,327 foreclosures.[149] Sales of existing homes for February 2010 was 11,890, up 21% from the same month in 2009. Only two metropolitan areas showed a decrease in homes sold: Panama City and Brevard County. The average sales price for an existing house was $131,000, 7% decrease from the prior year.[150][dubious â discuss]
doc.after: Tourism makes up the largest sector of the state economy.[citation needed] Warm weather, sunshine, and hundreds of miles of beaches attract over 60 million visitors to the state every year. Florida was the top destination state in 2011.[151] About 28.4 million tourists visited Florida between January-March 2015, setting a record for attendance in that quarter.[152]
